WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:03.307
We need to be able
to call a lawyer.

00:03.351 --> 00:04.439
-I already called one.
-You don't know any lawyers.

00:04.482 --> 00:05.875
Yes, I do,
and he's on his way.

00:05.918 --> 00:08.008
I am running out of time.
You were in Cuba.

00:08.051 --> 00:09.574
Your father stole your children
to his palace.

00:09.618 --> 00:10.923
We have the coordinates.

00:10.967 --> 00:12.795
You were running this ass
as collateral.

00:12.838 --> 00:14.231
What the hell is
this ass?

00:15.232 --> 00:18.322
♪♪

00:18.366 --> 00:20.629
Rise and shine,
Gummy Bear.

00:22.805 --> 00:24.807
Daddy's here.

00:24.850 --> 00:26.374
What's happening?
Where am I?

00:26.417 --> 00:27.636
You're home.

00:27.679 --> 00:28.767
Where are my children?

00:28.811 --> 00:30.073
You mean
my grandchildren.

00:30.117 --> 00:32.423
Nate?!
Nate! Where are you?!

00:32.467 --> 00:34.382
[ Chuckling ] Hey!

00:34.425 --> 00:36.079
Look who's up,
sleepy head.

00:36.123 --> 00:37.820
Why didn't you
wake me up?!

00:37.863 --> 00:39.865
You were sleeping --
like an angel.

00:39.909 --> 00:41.693
It reminded me
of when you were little

00:41.737 --> 00:42.912
and I came into your room.

00:42.955 --> 00:45.523
It was late,
and you were sleeping,

00:45.567 --> 00:47.395
just like you were
a few minutes ago.

00:49.397 --> 00:51.312
That's a real shitty story.

00:51.355 --> 00:52.704
-Hey, look --
-Oh.

00:52.748 --> 00:55.446
have a hot bath,
have some hot coffee.

00:55.490 --> 00:57.535
Everything's hot down here.
You're gonna feel great.

00:57.579 --> 01:00.321
Need I remind you,
this maniac kidnapped our ch--

01:00.364 --> 01:01.409
Are you drinking?

01:01.452 --> 01:03.150
Mm? No, it's a mojito.

01:03.193 --> 01:04.499
That's drinking.

01:04.542 --> 01:06.283
Uh, no.
It's more like a wet salad.

01:06.327 --> 01:08.372
What?
But, still,
I am a fiend for these things.

01:08.416 --> 01:09.547
It's the mint
from the garden --

01:09.591 --> 01:11.375
This isn't a vacation,
Nate!

01:11.419 --> 01:13.508
Hey, look,
I know you're upset,

01:13.551 --> 01:16.293
and, trust me,
when I woke up, I was livid.

01:16.337 --> 01:17.729
[ Groaning ]

01:17.773 --> 01:19.949
[ Latin music playing ]

01:23.170 --> 01:24.214
What's happening?

01:24.258 --> 01:26.434
Buenos días, señor.

01:29.176 --> 01:30.655
Where am I?

01:33.441 --> 01:34.485
Huh?

01:41.101 --> 01:42.537
Unh...

01:42.580 --> 01:45.105
[ Chuckling ] But now
I feel like a new man.

01:45.148 --> 01:46.280
Seriously.[ Knock on door ]

01:46.323 --> 01:48.630
[ Sighs ] I don't --

01:48.673 --> 01:50.806
Buenos días,
señora.

01:50.849 --> 01:52.460
[ Clears throat ]
Robin, Carlita.

01:52.503 --> 01:55.985
Carlita, Robin --
uh, mi esposa.

01:56.028 --> 01:57.856
Well, not really.
One day, no?

01:57.900 --> 01:59.945
I promise.
That's what this is for.

01:59.989 --> 02:01.382
We'll get to it.

02:01.425 --> 02:03.993
She's --
Okay, you're friends.

02:05.734 --> 02:08.302
♪ Somewhere behind the skyline

02:08.345 --> 02:10.869
♪ There is a place
I'm thinkin' ♪

02:10.913 --> 02:14.134
[ Distorted music plays ]

02:16.962 --> 02:18.268
Kids? Kids?!

02:18.312 --> 02:19.617
I got to see my kids.

02:19.661 --> 02:21.010
Babe, no, they're fine.
I saw them.

02:21.053 --> 02:22.316
They're great.
They're having a great time.

02:22.359 --> 02:24.144
Easy, Gummy Bear.
You're dehydrated.

02:24.187 --> 02:25.884
Don't call me that.

02:25.928 --> 02:27.321
How did we get here?

02:28.235 --> 02:30.193
Oh. Yes. Dude.
Thank you so much.

02:30.237 --> 02:31.455
Really appreciate that.

02:31.499 --> 02:33.065
The Internet's
so bad down here.

02:33.109 --> 02:34.502
I just want to see what --Nate, Nate, Nate!

02:34.545 --> 02:35.677
That's mad mask man
who was following us!

02:35.720 --> 02:36.939
-Who -- Conrad?
-Yeah.

02:36.982 --> 02:39.202
He's my transpo captain.He's terrifying.

02:39.246 --> 02:41.944
Oh, that's the nebulizer.
He's got crippling asthma.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.817
See?
No, he was gonna take you
to the airport,

02:45.861 --> 02:48.168
but then you decided
to driveyourself to Florida.

02:48.211 --> 02:49.473
And you call mea maniac.

02:51.214 --> 02:52.389
She peed in the van.

02:54.261 --> 02:56.480
I don't know. It's like
trying to fill up a shot
glass with a wet sponge.

02:56.524 --> 02:58.308
And then I had him
get you a helicopter,

02:58.352 --> 03:00.571
but you jumped
on some stupid fishing boat.

03:00.615 --> 03:02.834
And this idiot
ran it up on the dock.

03:04.358 --> 03:06.229
Who doesn't know
how to drive a boat?

03:06.273 --> 03:09.014
You just point it straight
and go.
I'm not a boat guy.

03:09.058 --> 03:11.713
You don't have to be a boat guy
to drive it out of a slip.

03:11.756 --> 03:14.063
All right, once again,
how did we get here?

03:14.106 --> 03:15.238
Did you drug us
or something?

03:15.282 --> 03:16.674
We found you asleep.

03:16.718 --> 03:18.502
We were awake
for 48 hours straight, okay?

03:18.546 --> 03:19.982
We just passed out.

03:22.289 --> 03:24.073
Just like that one time
I carried you

03:24.116 --> 03:26.293
when you were little
and you didn't even stir.

03:26.336 --> 03:28.991
God! Your stories of my youth
suck so bad!

03:29.034 --> 03:30.514
Okay, okay, look.

03:30.558 --> 03:32.342
What's done is done.
You're here.

03:32.386 --> 03:34.910
And I've got
a pretty big surprise for you.Oh, do you?

03:34.953 --> 03:37.521
Is it even a bigger surprise
than you kidnapping my children

03:37.565 --> 03:39.044
for a worthless
piece of metal?

03:39.088 --> 03:41.133
I told you,
that's not what it's about.

03:41.177 --> 03:42.918
He's not a bad guy.

03:42.961 --> 03:45.225
You've been brainwashed, Nate.
You've been rubbed out.

03:45.268 --> 03:46.574
No!
I told her to stop!

03:46.617 --> 03:48.053
Right? Hi.

03:48.097 --> 03:50.578
This is all about my love
for you and your family.

03:50.621 --> 03:52.362
[ Sighs ]
I don't need your love.

03:52.406 --> 03:54.712
I have all the love I need
from my ownfamily.

03:54.756 --> 03:55.844
I hate you!

03:55.887 --> 03:57.672
No, you --
Don't say that!

03:57.715 --> 03:58.803
I want to stay!

03:58.847 --> 04:00.283
Well, you can't!

04:00.327 --> 04:01.850
Pee-Paw said we could stay
as long as we want.

04:01.893 --> 04:02.981
Such a stupid name.

04:03.025 --> 04:04.374
We came up with
that name!

04:04.418 --> 04:05.767
Yeah.

04:05.810 --> 04:07.551
He's the best.
I mean, he lets us swear.

04:07.595 --> 04:09.727
Hey! You're not allowed
to swear!

04:09.771 --> 04:11.512
You're such a [bleep]
What?!

04:11.555 --> 04:14.602
Don't you ever, ever
use that horrible word again!

04:14.645 --> 04:16.473
It's actually a pretty good
word. It means so many things.

04:16.517 --> 04:17.866
You're never allowed
to use it.

04:17.909 --> 04:19.171
It's almost every other word
in Scotland.

04:19.215 --> 04:20.869
You're not in Scotland!
Okay.

04:20.912 --> 04:22.914
What if I'm on a Scottish beach
and I get sand in my [bleep]?

04:22.958 --> 04:24.264
-No! Shh!
-No!

04:24.307 --> 04:25.352
Close your lips!

04:25.395 --> 04:27.049
Downstairs lady lips
also means --

04:27.092 --> 04:29.486
-No! Stop talking!
-No! No!

04:29.530 --> 04:32.054
The only reason I am keeping
any kind of composure

04:32.097 --> 04:33.969
is because I know
he is manipulating you.

04:34.012 --> 04:35.449
And you're not?!No!

04:35.492 --> 04:37.494
I'm -- I'm trying to do
what's best for you.

04:37.538 --> 04:38.843
You made us live
in a trailer

04:38.887 --> 04:40.280
when we could have been
living here!

04:42.412 --> 04:44.893
Can you help me, please?

04:44.936 --> 04:46.634
He's not wrong
on that one.

04:46.677 --> 04:47.635
Oh, my Go--

04:47.678 --> 04:48.897
Guys, listen to me.

04:48.940 --> 04:50.464
This place was built
on dirty money.

04:50.507 --> 04:52.640
I don't want that kind
of influence on you guys.

04:52.683 --> 04:54.511
Listen, I get that,
but...

04:54.555 --> 04:56.208
I get the feeling
he's trying to go legit.

04:56.252 --> 04:58.907
Ugh! You're so gullible.
He's a professional lair, Nate.

04:58.950 --> 05:00.212
So are you!

05:00.256 --> 05:01.997
We have a grandfather
our whole lives,

05:02.040 --> 05:03.738
and you kept him from us.

05:03.781 --> 05:04.826
Because he's a criminal!

05:04.869 --> 05:06.044
And you're not?

05:07.219 --> 05:08.743
Is that
Dick Cheney?

05:08.786 --> 05:10.222
Yeah, probably is.

05:10.266 --> 05:12.486
Yeah. Pee-Paw's selling him
something secret.

05:12.529 --> 05:15.140
He was waiting on some
stupid mule to bring an ass.

05:17.012 --> 05:19.275
You don't go legit
all at once.

05:21.973 --> 05:23.366
You're right.

05:23.410 --> 05:24.759
Wait. What? I am?
I'm right?

05:24.802 --> 05:26.413
Mm-hmm. You areright.
You're right.

05:26.456 --> 05:27.762
Sorry. God!
I'm sorry.

05:27.805 --> 05:29.633
I'm just --
I'm being so childish.

05:29.677 --> 05:31.722
I mean,
who am I as their mother

05:31.766 --> 05:34.290
to say they can't just
spew profanity?

05:34.334 --> 05:35.596
Within reason,
you know?

05:35.639 --> 05:37.902
And this guy --
he's a businessman.

05:37.946 --> 05:41.297
He deals in exotic trade
with influential people.

05:41.341 --> 05:43.255
I get it.
It's a living.

05:43.299 --> 05:45.345
It's unique, sure.
You know?
It is. It is.

05:45.388 --> 05:47.129
Wait.
So we can stay?

05:47.172 --> 05:48.652
You bet.
You can stay.

05:48.696 --> 05:50.698
I have an idea.
Why don't you guys stay here.

05:50.741 --> 05:53.135
I'm gonna go to town,
and I'm gonna get my own
little surprise for Paw-Paw.

05:53.178 --> 05:54.658
-It's "Pee-Paw."
-It's stupid.

05:54.702 --> 05:56.312
Wait. Hold on.
You sure you're okay with this?

05:56.356 --> 05:57.879
That was a real quick turn
you just did there.

05:57.922 --> 05:59.402
Yeah, no.
I know, I know, I know.

05:59.446 --> 06:01.491
I'm great, though.
I am. I'm good. I just --

06:01.535 --> 06:03.841
I feel like I need to put an end
to this feud once and for all,

06:03.885 --> 06:05.669
you know, for the sake
of all of us, for our future.

06:05.713 --> 06:07.410
Sure. Yeah. You want me
to go to town with you?

06:07.454 --> 06:09.281
No. Nah. This is something
I'm gonna do on my own.

06:09.325 --> 06:11.762
You just stay here, you guys.
Stay here and relax.

06:11.806 --> 06:13.155
You know what?
I willrelax.
Great.

06:13.198 --> 06:15.113
'Cause, unlike when I tell you,
I listen.

06:15.157 --> 06:16.898
You know, I go, "Yes.

06:16.941 --> 06:19.204
I should relax, babe.
I'm too tense."
'Kay.

06:19.248 --> 06:20.815
You know,
maybe I'll get a massage.

06:20.858 --> 06:21.859
From, uh...

06:21.903 --> 06:23.731
Hey!

06:23.774 --> 06:25.080
That's my friend
over there.

06:25.123 --> 06:26.342
Okay, good, good.

06:30.433 --> 06:32.522
[ Latin music playing ]

06:38.093 --> 06:41.488
Yeah. It's the mojitos.
I think they loosen up my hips.

06:46.623 --> 06:47.885
[ Chuckles ]
Speaking of which,

06:47.929 --> 06:49.539
this ice is safe to drink,
right?

06:51.280 --> 06:52.499
I don't want to get sick.[ Clears throat ]

06:52.542 --> 06:54.414
Oh, hey. Sorry.
Sorry, sir.

06:54.457 --> 06:55.632
[ Clears throat ]
She asked me to dance.

06:55.676 --> 06:57.373
I thought it would be rude
if I said no.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.244
You know,
it's custom and everything.

06:59.288 --> 07:01.377
I know it looks sensual,
but it's, apparently, not sexual

07:01.421 --> 07:03.118
in any way, shape, or form.

07:03.161 --> 07:04.641
Sure it is.

07:04.685 --> 07:06.382
Um...I'm still very much
in love with your daughter --

07:06.426 --> 07:09.167
deep, deep, deep,
deeply in love with her.

07:09.211 --> 07:10.821
And, uh...

07:10.865 --> 07:12.780
I don't know why I'm so nervous
around you all of a sudden.

07:12.823 --> 07:14.390
It's weird, you know.

07:14.434 --> 07:17.001
I've never gone through
this father-in-law thing before.

07:17.045 --> 07:18.960
But, uh...you know,
I just wanted to say

07:19.003 --> 07:21.571
from the bottom of my heart,
I speak for my whole family

07:21.615 --> 07:23.268
when I say, uh...

07:23.312 --> 07:24.574
you know...

07:26.707 --> 07:28.752
...I love you, Dad.

07:28.796 --> 07:30.188
Okay.
That was weird.
That was weird.

07:30.232 --> 07:31.755
It was weird.
It was too much, too quick.

07:31.799 --> 07:33.496
I get it, I get it.
It's the mojitos talking.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.977
I want to make something
perfectly clear.
Sure.

07:36.020 --> 07:37.413
I would have done
the same thing

07:37.457 --> 07:39.284
for anyguy
Robin settled down with.

07:39.328 --> 07:40.590
Right.

07:40.634 --> 07:42.462
Sorry. I'm not --
I'm not following you.

07:42.505 --> 07:46.553
Everything you have in your life
is because of me.

07:46.596 --> 07:48.816
No, I kn-- I'm thankful for you
setting me up in New York.

07:48.859 --> 07:50.818
You know, it was a little weird
how you did it, but, you know --

07:50.861 --> 07:52.515
I had a life before that.
I had a job.

07:52.559 --> 07:54.169
Did you?

07:54.212 --> 07:57.389
You were a part-time lab monkey
at PFR when you met her.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.827
I called my mountaineering
buddy, Mr. Gupta,

07:59.870 --> 08:01.568
and the next day,
you were an executive.

08:01.611 --> 08:03.570
You didn't think
that was kind of weird?

08:03.613 --> 08:05.876
Thought it was
'cause I was doing a good job.

08:10.011 --> 08:12.970
You are nothing
without me.

08:15.669 --> 08:18.498
Enjoy the party, Nate.

08:18.541 --> 08:21.065
And lose the hat.
Makes you look like a douche.

08:22.458 --> 08:25.287
S-Same hat.

08:25.330 --> 08:27.245
[ Music continues ]

08:27.289 --> 08:30.292
Robin: Why is it always raining
in this valley?!

08:30.335 --> 08:31.293
Cuba!

08:31.336 --> 08:32.468
[ Thunder rumbles ]

08:32.512 --> 08:34.165
Good God!

08:34.209 --> 08:36.516
[ Applause ]

08:37.168 --> 08:38.430
J.R.: Hola.

08:38.474 --> 08:39.780
I want to thank you all
for coming

08:39.823 --> 08:42.086
to this exciting unveiling.

08:42.130 --> 08:45.307
This iconic statue
has taken decades

08:45.350 --> 08:47.048
to finally come back together --

08:47.091 --> 08:48.440
a piece of history.

08:48.484 --> 08:50.225
It was thought
to have been destroyed.

08:50.268 --> 08:51.748
It's now fully restored

08:51.792 --> 08:56.013
and is now the prized possession
of this gentleman.

09:02.846 --> 09:05.936
My daughter, Robin,
was supposed to be here,

09:05.980 --> 09:08.635
but her children
and their father --

09:08.678 --> 09:10.941
who I know is appreciative
of all this --

09:10.985 --> 09:11.942
they're here.

09:11.986 --> 09:14.205
Nate, kids, take a bow.

09:14.249 --> 09:17.513
[ Applause ]

09:17.557 --> 09:20.124
This is all for you guys.

09:20.168 --> 09:21.343
Sit down, Nate.

09:21.386 --> 09:22.518
Yeah.

09:24.172 --> 09:26.348
Not everyone here knows

09:26.391 --> 09:28.829
that I was born
with next to nothing.

09:28.872 --> 09:31.875
And the only way I could provide
for my one and only daughter

09:31.919 --> 09:33.703
was to work hard.

09:33.747 --> 09:36.227
Did I cut a few corners?Dick: Show me
the Goddamn statue.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.100
Okay.

09:39.143 --> 09:40.275
Here we go.

09:40.318 --> 09:43.844
[ Middle Eastern music plays ]

09:49.980 --> 09:51.852
Holy shit!

09:53.810 --> 09:55.464
How did you get that?

09:57.901 --> 10:00.643
[ Indistinct shouting ]

10:00.687 --> 10:04.560
♪♪

10:04.604 --> 10:05.996
J.R.: Great.

10:06.040 --> 10:09.521
Head right in here, boys.
Arms and legs, too.

10:09.565 --> 10:12.263
[ British accent ]
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

10:12.307 --> 10:13.961
W-W-W-W-Who are
you chaps with?

10:14.004 --> 10:15.832
Who do you think?Ain't that the truth.

10:15.876 --> 10:18.879
I count about 32 Iraqis
and 600 bloody journalists.

10:18.922 --> 10:21.664
It's the most staged photo op
since Iwo Jima.

10:21.708 --> 10:24.145
You must be envious of the lads
who served during the Raj.

10:24.188 --> 10:26.103
Ooh.
No media, no pressure --

10:26.147 --> 10:27.757
just the beauties
of Colonial India.

10:27.801 --> 10:29.498
Oh, you know --
you know the Indians --

10:29.541 --> 10:31.021
a civilized people.

10:31.065 --> 10:32.762
Exactly.
Took a while,
but they got there.

10:32.806 --> 10:34.634
Yeah.
T-They got there.

10:34.677 --> 10:36.766
Still, you know what? I'm not
sure you can take this stuff.

10:36.810 --> 10:38.289
Why not?

10:38.333 --> 10:40.422
Well, 'cause this property
belongs to, um...

10:40.465 --> 10:42.076
Well,
I'm not technically sure

10:42.119 --> 10:43.947
whoit belongs to
right now, but...

10:43.991 --> 10:45.601
Then what's it to you?

10:45.645 --> 10:47.342
Ah, that's actually
a good point.

10:47.385 --> 10:49.910
You know, we're only here 'cause
Blair is Bush's golf buddy.

10:49.953 --> 10:51.694
Who singularly failed
to learn the lessons

10:51.738 --> 10:54.044
of hundreds of years
of failed nation-building.

10:54.088 --> 10:55.698
Right?
Mm.

10:55.742 --> 10:57.700
Still, it does beat London
in the winter,

10:57.744 --> 10:59.571
and the kebabs are decent.

10:59.615 --> 11:00.572
Not bad. Not bad.

11:00.616 --> 11:02.313
Eh...
You know what?

11:02.357 --> 11:04.402
These people are just gonna
whack it with sticks anyway

11:04.446 --> 11:07.188
and shove bottle rockets
in it.

11:07.231 --> 11:08.798
As you were. Carry on.

11:08.842 --> 11:10.278
God save the queen.

11:10.321 --> 11:12.497
Oh, keep it under your hat.
Naughty.

11:12.541 --> 11:14.195
God, you are so cool.

11:14.238 --> 11:15.326
[ Chuckles ]

11:17.154 --> 11:18.765
There's a hole
in the back.

11:18.808 --> 11:22.116
Ah, yes --
the pièce de résistance.

11:22.159 --> 11:23.421
[ Snaps fingers ]

11:24.901 --> 11:26.686
[ Crowd gasping, chuckling ]

11:29.427 --> 11:32.213
Jesus Christ. We were
carrying around the ass
of Saddam Hussein?

11:32.256 --> 11:33.736
Mm-hmm.

11:33.780 --> 11:36.608
And that ass just made you
a cool $10 million.

11:36.652 --> 11:37.827
Surprise!

11:37.871 --> 11:39.307
Sorry. What?

11:39.350 --> 11:41.962
That was my surprise --
a life of freedom.

11:42.005 --> 11:44.312
10 million American dollars,
not Cuban?

11:44.355 --> 11:45.792
Yeah.

11:47.271 --> 11:49.621
Remember before, when I said
I love you and I took it back?

11:49.665 --> 11:51.188
I don't give a shit.
I love you, man.

11:51.232 --> 11:53.147
No, no, no, no, no.Okay, all right.

11:53.190 --> 11:54.626
$10 million! What?!

11:54.670 --> 11:57.151
[ Laughter ]

11:57.194 --> 11:58.979
Everybody out!
Party's over!

11:59.022 --> 12:00.850
[ Crowd screaming ]Oh, shoot. Babe?

12:00.894 --> 12:02.373
Nate, keep the kids safe.

12:02.417 --> 12:03.810
Oh, my God.

12:03.853 --> 12:05.681
All right, guys,
get down, get down. Get down.

12:05.725 --> 12:08.249
I knew you couldn't change.
You're incapable of change!

12:08.292 --> 12:10.555
You may have tricked
my stupid family,

12:10.599 --> 12:12.427
but you will
never trick me.

12:12.470 --> 12:13.602
That'll do, Robin.

12:13.645 --> 12:15.473
What'd you just say?

12:15.517 --> 12:16.736
That'll do.

12:16.779 --> 12:18.825
Babe!Nate! Stay out of this!

12:18.868 --> 12:20.740
He's not gonna make any money
off of this deal.

12:20.783 --> 12:22.567
Yeah, I know!Nobody is!

12:22.611 --> 12:24.613
You can blow it
out your ass!

12:25.353 --> 12:26.571
W-What's she doing?

12:26.615 --> 12:27.747
I don't know!
She's crazy!

12:29.705 --> 12:31.359
Oh, shit!No, don't do that!

12:31.402 --> 12:32.708
No!

12:32.752 --> 12:34.231
It keeps coming out!

12:34.275 --> 12:38.018
What is wrong with you?!
Our children are here!

12:38.061 --> 12:39.280
What are you doing?!

12:39.323 --> 12:41.369
Oh! Wait!
Jesus Christ! Come on!

12:50.770 --> 12:52.032
[ Groans ] Owwww!

12:52.075 --> 12:53.033
Aaah!

12:53.076 --> 12:54.164
Oh! Are you okay?

12:54.208 --> 12:55.731
[ Groaning ]

12:55.775 --> 12:57.602
[ Whining ] No!

12:58.952 --> 13:00.257
Ow!

13:05.697 --> 13:07.787
[ Both panting ]

13:19.146 --> 13:20.495
Well...

13:20.538 --> 13:22.149
there you have it.

13:23.193 --> 13:24.368
See you 'round, kids.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.327
♪♪

13:37.164 --> 13:39.209
♪♪

13:39.514 --> 13:41.385
[ Engine shuts off ]Nate: What are you doing?

13:41.429 --> 13:43.039
Robin: Will somebody
please talk to me?

13:43.083 --> 13:44.519
What are you
talking about?

13:44.562 --> 13:45.999
I'm not gonna have
my family looking at me

13:46.042 --> 13:47.217
with resentment,
all right?

13:47.261 --> 13:48.523
You guys,
I know I screwed up,

13:48.566 --> 13:49.916
but we're gonna
get through this.

13:49.959 --> 13:51.395
It's over.
We have nothing.

13:51.439 --> 13:52.962
What are you t--
We have each other!

13:53.006 --> 13:54.616
If you weren't so stubborn,

13:54.659 --> 13:56.705
we'd "have each other"
on a private jet right now.

13:56.748 --> 13:58.576
How was that,
by the way?It was pretty awesome.

13:58.620 --> 13:59.969
We played turbulence Jenga.

14:00.013 --> 14:01.405
You know
what I don't get?
What?

14:01.449 --> 14:03.103
Even though
your father was just --

14:03.146 --> 14:05.540
Aggressively in our shit?!Yes.

14:05.583 --> 14:06.671
Why that matters, though.

14:06.715 --> 14:07.890
Ever since I've met you,

14:07.934 --> 14:09.239
all you've wanted to do
is be rich.

14:09.283 --> 14:11.415
No, I wanted us
to be rich.

14:11.459 --> 14:13.287
I wanted usto earn it.

14:13.330 --> 14:14.592
I don't want to earn it.

14:14.636 --> 14:16.420
Yeah, I want to have it,
then spend it.

14:16.464 --> 14:18.770
It was guilt money.Stop putting adjectives
in front of it.

14:18.814 --> 14:20.511
It's just money.
No, it's not!

14:20.555 --> 14:22.644
It's a "Refund
for shitty parenting" money.

14:22.687 --> 14:24.951
I don't care if it's "Sorry
I slept with your sister" money!

14:24.994 --> 14:26.822
Which I didn't...
at all.

14:26.866 --> 14:28.780
That'd be gross.Why would you do that?

14:28.824 --> 14:30.043
It's still money.

14:31.044 --> 14:32.306
Yeah, but --
Okay, guys, even --

14:32.349 --> 14:34.961
even if we took it,
then what?

14:35.004 --> 14:36.440
Right? I mean,
don't you get it?

14:36.484 --> 14:37.877
No!No!No!

14:37.920 --> 14:39.443
Don't you think
he would screw us over?

14:39.487 --> 14:40.923
No!No!No!

14:40.967 --> 14:43.317
[ Sighs ]

14:43.360 --> 14:44.840
Do you think
I'm being too proud?

14:44.884 --> 14:46.842
Yes!Yes!No! Yes!

14:46.886 --> 14:48.931
No? Well,
I don't know which one to pick.

14:48.975 --> 14:51.020
Look,
you blew away $20 million.

14:51.064 --> 14:52.239
It was only 10.
Whatever.

14:52.282 --> 14:54.284
That's still
a shit ton of money, okay?

14:54.328 --> 14:55.851
Back in Cuba,

14:55.895 --> 14:58.332
there was a mansion
called the Robin's Nest,

14:58.375 --> 15:00.421
and we're not living in it.

15:00.464 --> 15:02.858
We could go back there
and start a new life.

15:05.861 --> 15:07.558
Is this what you all
want to do?

15:07.602 --> 15:08.864
Yes!Yes!Yes!

15:08.908 --> 15:10.910
[ Sighs ]

15:14.739 --> 15:16.437
Okay, turn it around.

15:16.480 --> 15:17.960
Really?
Yes!

15:18.004 --> 15:20.615
[ Cheering ]

15:20.658 --> 15:22.225
[ Laughter ]

15:22.269 --> 15:24.097
Come on.
Let's go to Cooba!

15:24.140 --> 15:25.098
Whoo!
Get some!

15:25.141 --> 15:26.316
Cuba!
Get some!

15:26.360 --> 15:28.014
[ Engine sputtering ]

15:28.057 --> 15:29.015
Uh, just go.

15:29.058 --> 15:31.147
Just...relax.

15:31.191 --> 15:33.019
[ Clicking ]

15:33.062 --> 15:34.585
Dad,
quit screwing around.

15:34.629 --> 15:37.023
I'm not screwing around!
I'm trying to start the motor.

15:39.895 --> 15:41.027
What's up?

15:41.070 --> 15:43.116
I don't know!
I'm not a boat guy!

15:43.159 --> 15:44.813
♪♪

15:49.861 --> 15:51.559
Daddy, are we gonna die?

15:51.602 --> 15:53.735
No! No,
we're not gonna die, okay?

15:53.778 --> 15:56.303
We're gonna be fine.
This is the Straits of Florida.

15:56.346 --> 15:58.870
All right? It's a very highly
traveled body of water.

15:58.914 --> 16:00.394
Someone's gonna find us.

16:02.352 --> 16:03.701
Eventually.

16:06.008 --> 16:08.445
[ Bird squawking ]

16:08.489 --> 16:10.491
♪♪

16:18.499 --> 16:19.456
Are you praying?

16:19.500 --> 16:20.457
Jesus Christ.

16:20.501 --> 16:22.459
Yes, I'm praying, okay?

16:22.503 --> 16:24.026
Is there anything wrong
with praying

16:24.070 --> 16:25.506
for a raft
to come find us?

16:25.549 --> 16:26.898
What's that?!

16:26.942 --> 16:28.335
What is that?

16:28.378 --> 16:30.685
That's a raft.
Whoa. Whoa!

16:30.728 --> 16:32.426
[ Laughter ]

16:32.469 --> 16:33.644
That's a raft!

16:33.688 --> 16:35.429
You should've prayed
for a Jet Ski.

16:35.472 --> 16:37.170
[ Indistinct shouting ]

16:37.213 --> 16:39.085
-Over here!
-Save us!

16:39.128 --> 16:40.869
Americana!

16:41.652 --> 16:43.045
Here you go.

16:43.089 --> 16:45.265
Ah, thank you guys so much.
Thank you so, so much.

16:45.308 --> 16:46.527
Everybody on board.
Let's go.

16:46.570 --> 16:47.876
Oh, thank you.
Thank God.

16:47.919 --> 16:49.399
Okay, everybody on board.
Vamos.

16:49.443 --> 16:51.140
No, no, no, no! No, no.
Our boat's broken.

16:51.184 --> 16:53.403
O-Or out of gas. I don't know.
I'm not a boat guy.

16:53.447 --> 16:54.970
Our boat is shit.

17:00.410 --> 17:03.022
Hey, I'm sorry --
no more room.

17:03.065 --> 17:04.806
What? No!
No, please, please.

17:04.849 --> 17:06.938
You got room there.
We could squeeze.

17:06.982 --> 17:08.592
We're small.

17:08.636 --> 17:10.986
Take the kids, okay?
And -- And her.

17:11.030 --> 17:12.379
Niños, sí,okay.

17:12.422 --> 17:14.076
Not the woman.
Wha--

17:14.120 --> 17:15.817
Hey, amigo!
Mucho dinero.

17:15.860 --> 17:17.384
What did you just give him?

17:17.427 --> 17:19.081
Well, Pee-Paw gave us
some late birthday money.

17:19.125 --> 17:21.953
How much did you give him?I don't know --
like $800.

17:21.997 --> 17:24.130
This is at least $60,000!

17:24.173 --> 17:25.261
Sorry. What?

17:25.305 --> 17:26.871
I was
just trying to help.

17:26.915 --> 17:28.612
$60,000?!

17:28.656 --> 17:30.223
Hey, okay!
Everybody on board!

17:30.266 --> 17:32.007
Come on. Even the woman.
Ta bien.

17:32.051 --> 17:34.053
Okay, all right.
Let's get on. Come on.

17:34.096 --> 17:35.706
You saved us,
but you really overpaid.

17:35.750 --> 17:36.881
All right.

17:36.925 --> 17:39.058
♪♪

17:42.017 --> 17:44.280
So, uh...

17:44.324 --> 17:46.239
how long does it take
to get back to Cuba?

17:46.282 --> 17:47.675
[ Chuckling ]
We're not going to Cuba.

17:47.718 --> 17:49.546
Never again!
Cuba is shit!

17:49.590 --> 17:51.505
[ Cheering ]We go America.

17:51.548 --> 17:52.767
[ Cheering ]

17:52.810 --> 17:54.508
No, no, no, no.
We're going to Cuba.

17:54.551 --> 17:56.292
Why would we want to go there?
It's shit!

17:56.336 --> 17:57.946
[ Indistinct shouting ]

17:57.989 --> 17:59.513
No, it's not.
It's awesome.

17:59.556 --> 18:01.819
I suppose if you have money,
like yourself.

18:01.863 --> 18:03.604
But for most of us,
it's shit.

18:03.647 --> 18:05.736
Well, how long is it gonna take
for us to get to America?

18:05.780 --> 18:08.609
Um...eight days,
give or take.

18:08.652 --> 18:10.393
But don't worry.
We'll make plenty of stops.

18:10.437 --> 18:11.438
Okay? [ Chuckles ]

18:11.481 --> 18:13.048
iAdios,Cooba!

18:13.092 --> 18:15.311
[ Cheering ]

18:15.355 --> 18:17.313
Hecalls it "Cooba."

18:17.357 --> 18:18.662
Okay.

18:22.492 --> 18:23.972
♪♪

18:32.459 --> 18:33.808
Are we bad parents?

18:33.851 --> 18:35.592
[ Coughs, spits ]

18:35.636 --> 18:37.072
Yes.

18:37.116 --> 18:38.987
We're the [bleep] worst.

18:39.030 --> 18:42.251
We are the [bleep]
worst parents ever.

18:42.295 --> 18:44.993
Jesus Christ.
We're going back to nothing.

18:45.036 --> 18:47.256
I know, but we're gonna
make it work.

18:47.300 --> 18:48.301
Where?!

18:48.344 --> 18:49.563
Syracuse.

18:49.606 --> 18:50.738
Syracuse sucks!

18:50.781 --> 18:52.087
Okay,
we'll go to New York.

18:52.131 --> 18:53.958
There's nothing in New York
for us.

18:54.002 --> 18:55.438
Florida.
We're so close.

18:55.482 --> 18:56.961
You want
to live in Florida?

18:57.005 --> 18:59.138
You know,
you guys complain a lot.

18:59.181 --> 19:00.965
Is that what the rest
of America's like?

19:01.009 --> 19:02.445
Pretty much.

19:02.489 --> 19:04.099
America's the greatest country
in the world.

19:04.143 --> 19:06.014
Unh...used to be.

19:06.057 --> 19:08.451
Only people that grew up
with freedom don't like America.

19:08.495 --> 19:10.279
America on its worst day
is still better

19:10.323 --> 19:11.976
than Cuba on its best.

19:12.020 --> 19:13.717
We make it to land,

19:13.761 --> 19:15.458
your country takes us --
me, my family --

19:15.502 --> 19:18.635
and puts us in a hotel --
Swift Stay Suites.

19:18.679 --> 19:22.639
Air-conditioning, pool,
business center.

19:22.683 --> 19:25.642
32 cable channels, including
Ted Turner's Superstation.

19:25.686 --> 19:27.209
[ Chuckles ]

19:27.253 --> 19:29.646
That's the oppression
of infinite choice.

19:29.690 --> 19:31.692
Yeah, but then what?
Don't they just send you back?

19:31.735 --> 19:33.084
No, we make it to land,

19:33.128 --> 19:35.739
your country grants us
economic asylum.

19:35.783 --> 19:38.089
They send us to new places,
like Delaware

19:38.133 --> 19:39.743
or better -- Nebraska.

19:39.787 --> 19:41.745
We become whole new people.

19:41.789 --> 19:43.399
That's a great country.

19:46.837 --> 19:47.882
Sweetie.

19:48.578 --> 19:50.058
I'm sorry.

19:50.101 --> 19:52.539
Baby? Baby. Baby.
Sorry.

19:52.582 --> 19:54.628
♪♪

20:30.229 --> 20:31.317
Hey.

20:31.360 --> 20:32.666
Hmm?

20:32.709 --> 20:34.015
It's land.

20:34.058 --> 20:35.538
There's land there.

20:35.582 --> 20:37.148
What is that?

20:37.192 --> 20:38.933
[ Laughing ] America!

20:38.976 --> 20:40.543
That's the U.S.?
Yes!

20:40.587 --> 20:41.675
[ Laughter ]

20:41.718 --> 20:43.894
That's the U.S.!
No way!

20:43.938 --> 20:45.156
Hey!

20:45.200 --> 20:47.289
All right!

20:47.333 --> 20:50.205
We're gonna be okay.
We're gonna be all right.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.554
Weare.

20:51.598 --> 20:52.816
[ Laughs ]

20:52.860 --> 20:55.123
-Babe...
-We did it!

20:55.166 --> 20:56.603
[ Telephone rings ]

20:56.646 --> 20:57.604
Auspice.

20:57.647 --> 20:58.996
Jack Randall here.

20:59.040 --> 21:00.302
Listen.[ Whispering ]
Record this.

21:00.346 --> 21:01.956
Somebody record this.
Track this.

21:01.999 --> 21:04.045
I'm not the one you want.
It's my daughter.

21:04.088 --> 21:06.526
She's the brains
behind the whole thing.

21:06.569 --> 21:09.398
You dipshits have been chasing
the wrong Randall.

21:09.442 --> 21:11.966
And I'll tell you exactly where you can find her.

21:12.009 --> 21:13.097
You got a pencil?

21:13.141 --> 21:14.142
Pencil!
[ Snaps fingers ]

21:14.185 --> 21:15.535
I need a pencil!

21:15.578 --> 21:17.450
[ Normal voice ]
No, I said a Goddamn pencil!

21:17.493 --> 21:19.321
Man: This is
the United States Coast Guard!

21:19.365 --> 21:21.410
Swim, amigos!
Coast Guard!

21:21.454 --> 21:23.412
Wait, wait! We don't
have to swim. We're American.

21:23.456 --> 21:25.196
With a criminal record!
Let's swim!

21:25.240 --> 21:26.197
Okay, okay.

21:26.241 --> 21:27.286
[ Screams ]

21:29.810 --> 21:30.985
[ Gunfire ]

21:31.028 --> 21:32.726
Do not jump in the water!

21:32.769 --> 21:33.770
[ Delilah screams ]

21:33.814 --> 21:35.772
Do not jump in the water!

21:35.816 --> 21:38.340
[ Sirens wailing ]

21:38.384 --> 21:40.690
Edie and Carl: [ Rapping ]
♪ Mail, mail, we cannot fail

21:40.734 --> 21:43.171
♪ Through snow, rain,
sleet, or the hail ♪

21:43.214 --> 21:45.521
♪ From big cities
to small towns ♪

21:45.565 --> 21:47.088
♪ Nothing can keep
these couriers ♪

21:47.131 --> 21:48.829
♪ From their appointed rounds

21:48.872 --> 21:50.570
♪ I know you like to be frank,
so you can ♪

21:50.613 --> 21:52.398
♪ Take this to the bank♪♪ Be frank

21:52.441 --> 21:55.444
How the hell did we get
stuck working with
these assholes again?

21:55.488 --> 21:57.141
[ Air horns blaring ]Go! Go!

21:57.185 --> 21:59.448
[ People screaming ]

21:59.492 --> 22:01.668
You will be
arrested and prosecuted

22:01.711 --> 22:03.496
by the United States
government!

22:03.539 --> 22:04.714
[ Grunting ]

22:04.758 --> 22:05.933
What about Espartaco?!

22:08.762 --> 22:11.199
[ Man speaking Spanish
over speaker ]

22:11.242 --> 22:12.766
Come on! Come on!

22:12.809 --> 22:14.637
America!

22:14.681 --> 22:16.291
Oh, shit!

22:16.335 --> 22:18.554
Aw, shit! So close!

22:18.598 --> 22:20.730
♪♪

22:32.655 --> 22:34.483
We're going postal.

22:34.527 --> 22:37.094
♪♪

22:44.624 --> 22:47.191
[ Cheering ]

22:47.235 --> 22:49.368
♪♪

22:54.721 --> 22:57.071
[ Sighs ]

23:02.598 --> 23:04.948
Everybody,
hold your positions.

23:04.992 --> 23:06.428
I'm taking her down.

23:12.565 --> 23:14.218
Miss Randall?

23:14.262 --> 23:15.437
What?

23:15.481 --> 23:17.265
Uh, we need you
to come with us.

23:17.308 --> 23:19.702
I'm waiting for my dad.
He's supposed to meet me here.

23:19.746 --> 23:21.443
That's not
what he told us.

23:21.487 --> 23:23.837
Oh, looky, looky
what we have here.

23:25.752 --> 23:27.057
Where'd you get this?

23:27.101 --> 23:28.363
My dad gave it to me.

23:28.407 --> 23:29.669
How did he get it
to you?

23:29.712 --> 23:30.670
He mailed it.

23:30.713 --> 23:32.106
Exactly.

23:32.149 --> 23:34.369
Signed, sealed, delivered.

23:34.413 --> 23:36.240
♪♪

23:46.990 --> 23:49.993
[ Cheering ]

23:59.002 --> 24:00.961
Well, it was a little tougher
getting to the beach this time.

24:01.004 --> 24:02.745
Huh?
Yeah.

24:02.789 --> 24:05.269
You don't look bad
for eight days in a boat.

24:05.313 --> 24:06.923
Takes me like a year
to grow a beard.

24:06.967 --> 24:08.011
God, I know.

24:10.318 --> 24:11.711
We have the ass.

24:11.754 --> 24:13.843
We have a witness
turning State's in custody.

24:13.887 --> 24:15.845
We need him.
Give him to us!

24:15.889 --> 24:17.368
Or you and your family
are done.

24:17.412 --> 24:19.196
You don't mess with the mail.

24:21.372 --> 24:23.244
Just...

24:24.985 --> 24:25.986
Okay.

24:26.029 --> 24:28.118
Okay.
Okay, okay.

24:28.162 --> 24:30.294
[ Rock music plays ]

24:35.561 --> 24:36.736
[ Door opens ]

24:36.779 --> 24:37.998
Who the hell are you?

24:38.041 --> 24:39.565
Don't say
another Goddamn word!

24:39.608 --> 24:41.175
Him?!
He's great.

24:41.218 --> 24:43.786
He's --Joe Delicious,
divorce attorney.

24:43.830 --> 24:46.397
A federal agency
inquiring my clients

24:46.441 --> 24:49.139
without proper legal counsel
being present and accountable?

24:49.183 --> 24:52.142
Hmm? I mean,
did you even Mirandarize them?

24:52.186 --> 24:53.840
Did she Mirandarize you?

24:53.883 --> 24:55.755
No, she didn't.Ohhhh!

24:55.798 --> 24:58.105
I'm gonna have your badges,
you piece of shits.

24:58.148 --> 25:00.586
You kept my clients in here
for 6 1/2 hours

25:00.629 --> 25:02.370
without the right
to one of me's?

25:02.413 --> 25:04.981
You two -- up.
Let's go.

25:06.330 --> 25:07.897
Best wishes.
No.

25:07.941 --> 25:09.595
It's been fun.
Ugggh.

25:09.638 --> 25:10.900
This is not over!

25:10.944 --> 25:12.859
Oh, it sure as shit is,
scumbags.

25:12.902 --> 25:15.078
'Cause you're never
gonna find them again.

25:15.122 --> 25:16.384
[ Music ends ]

25:16.427 --> 25:18.038
This card is blank.

25:19.909 --> 25:22.608
[ Wind howling ]

25:22.651 --> 25:24.305
Do you guys have a pool?

25:24.348 --> 25:25.349
[ Slavic accent ] No.

25:25.393 --> 25:26.568
Business center?

25:26.612 --> 25:27.787
What's that?

25:27.830 --> 25:28.962
Could we take a look
at the menu?

25:29.005 --> 25:30.529
Food is behind you.

25:30.572 --> 25:32.443
What the hell is
all this?!

25:32.487 --> 25:34.576
It's xajib.

25:34.620 --> 25:36.491
And kobhaki.

25:36.535 --> 25:38.580
Okay, so, you have
one nonsmoking room.

25:38.624 --> 25:40.103
Oh, no.
